ttment to Jewish people everywhere, his profound and unwavering spirituality, his continual reminders of the very real dangers of pseudo-messianism and misplaced romantic zeal, and his willingness to take politically and religiously unpopular stands. Formulated as a companion volume to The Essential Agus, which presents selections of Agus' own writings, the contributors' analyses are based on specific selections of Agus' work which appear in The Essential Agus. Though each volume stands on its own, they are closely interconnected and readers will benefit from consulting both works.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aJewish scholarszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aJudaismzUnited States. 0aRabbiszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Religious.2bisacsh1 aBlumenthal, David R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDorff, Elliot N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFisher, Eugene J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGillman, Neil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKatz, Steven T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKatz, Steven T., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKaufman, William E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKonvitz, Milton R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLoeb, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNovak, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShargel, Norton D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWaxman, Mordecai, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyte